reviews.text: I've heard some call it "a dive". Other's have said, "hole in the wall". The sign says "Authentic Jamaican Cuisine". I just say, "I like it and the food is delicious."  The service is a little slow and the place shows wear and tear here and there but the food is very good and they have beer, wine and hard liquors. If you go, go there expecting great food, not a fancy atmosphere.

As a first generation West Indian I am very picky about WI food. It has been along time since I've been to a Caribbean restaurant that is like home cooking. I ordered king fish and an order of curry chicken.  To cut to the chase the food was excellent! I was very impressed and will how make The Jerk Pit my regular spot.

We are considering using their catering for a party so we came for a "tasting" of our own. The food is amazing!! Authentic flavors served up hot and fresh in generous portions with a vast selection of sides.We opted for oxtails with plaintain and red beans and rice. Also had jerk pork with yam and banana. 
The service is fast and the food comes out pretty quickly. The venue leaves a little to be desired. Love the Jamaican patois and expressions on the wall, but it is kind of dark and tightly configured.

This place is badly run. Tried to call several time to place an order no one answered. Went to the location, and was floored, the place was crowded no social distancing what so ever. No guidance from the workers nor management on social distancing of customers. I asked why no one answered the phone and was told that their policy is floor customers have priority. That’s well and good but it’s a pandemic out there! So I tried to place an order to be told that they needed to assist someone else first even though I was in line. Finally as I was standing there I noticed they were allowing individuals in the ordering area and restaurant with NO MASKS! I left... I feel god awful for the employees that have to deal with this. Grub hub workers were jumping in front of customers, again people with NO MASKS...Stay away, my lesson learned!

Food here is really good but getting thru to place a pick up order was a nightmare! The lines stayed busy it took me an hour for the phone to be picked up. When I got there they were really busy so it speaks to their good food but maybe they need multiple people on the phones. Its good to see a small business not suffering during this pandemic.
This spot gives awesome service and enjoyable menu. The best spot ever. The food and drinks arrived rapidly and the prices were inexpensive. I recommend this place.

Plenty of options  mainly seafood.  Good dessert options as well. Fairly priced. However most of the food was oversalted.  We arrived about 4pm and wait time and service was good.The place is very clean.

The reason for 2 stars is only the sweet tea and the hibachi grill cook. The food on the buffet was cold and this was our 1st time visiting here on a Friday night at 6pm. The selection of food is typical but the taste is not worth the cheap $13.99 dinner price. I will not visit here again.

The food is okay. It's a buffet restaurant, so it's an all-you-can eat restaurant at affordable prices for adults and children. Plus, there is a lot of variety and children under 2 eat for free. Last but not the least detail, it's an Asian restaurant (a Japanese restaurant I think), but you can also get Chinese food there. I will surely go back there...
Good crawfish but slow service on food that’s why I gave 3.5 star.

My absolute favorite buffet. Nothing compares to this one. Have been going for the last 18 years and the taste is timeless. Owners are so sweet, the ambience is amazing and I swear, the waitresses are so nice. Would definitely recommend. The pricing is worth what you eat. Restrooms are very clean and their parking availability is high. Love it.

Cheap is the best thing about this place.  Quality and variety are both below average.  The place was kind of dirty as well.  I dont think I would come back here as there are better options in the area.  On a positive note the host and server were very nice.

It is worth what you pay. Good food. Didn't break into the clarification of great and fancy food. Good, regular and tasty. I'd say good for college students testing themselves. Please have ambitions if you're taking someone on a date.

It's okay if you Chinese-American food. Not the best quality, but borderline decent. The nice part is that you can reserve sections for an event like a graduation. I've been going here occasionally since I was a kid. But there are definitely better places.

Still, it's a nice stopping place if you just need to eat, sit, then go in a reasonable time. Also tip the workers! They work hard.

Mixed review:  I was disappointed because I seen this place empty but on the Saturday noon time it was quite crowded and some Maryland Smart Talk was in, and the number of the available dishes disappointed me.  

If you see the price you'll notice it was under $10 on a Saturday and a drink comes with it.  Everything in the place is clean, now some hours later I'm not sick on the food.

Good clean fun! Updated alley is a nice place to take family, friend, or dates. Prices are reasonable and service is above board. Bar was also nice, but busy so be patient and the drinks will keep flowing. All in all a good time to be had by all, whether you're competitive or just looking for something active to get you moving. Enjoy!

I'm never going back.. 

I visited Bowlero last night with 10 friends and the experience from start to end was terrible.  

The 'security' checked my ID and asked me if I intended to drink alcohol, and then gave me a wristband - all for the bartender to ask me for my ID again.

The bar, took over 25 minutes to make drinks for me and the other 12 people waiting for drinks.. the bartenders seemed overwhelmed and weren’t very friendly or customer service oriented.. 

The food was meh..  the pizza is lower quality than little Caesar’s and the wings were on the brink of being undercooked...

And of the 4 lanes we paid for, 1 never worked and they refused to give my friend her money back for the lane because all the ones were booked together..

In short - don’t waste your time or money going to this place.. go somewhere in the city or to a smaller bowling alley in the area, because this spot misses the mark.

Bowling here can be a blast. The atmosphere is pretty great and really just brings the whole experience together. The drinks are a decent price, especially the 3 dollar long island iced teas. The whole package is a decent price, especially if you bring a bunch of friends. The only thing I cannot recommend is the food. The food is not bad by any means, but, in general, it is way too expensive. Make sure to eat before you come. Overall, we had a great experience and I expect to be back soon.

Fun atmosphere, nice patrons, mixed age crowd, and decent music. My nephew celebrated his 21st birthday amongst friends and family. I would recommend coming earlier than 8:45 pm to get lanes to bowl if you don't have a reservation. There were only two bartenders and they were SUPER busy. They did the best they could do mixing drinks for those sitting at the bar and bowlers, but the wait time was LONG. That's what made this review 4 out of 5 stars.

We as a Family 24 with three lanes had to me moved after waiting over a period of 30 to  45 minutes. Our lane number 9 was not resetting after every bowler so we were switched to lane 6 which in turn did the same thing several times.  We had to ask for help resetting the lanes at least six times doing our visit. This is a okay place would have been great if the racks worked properly staff stands around talking and you practically have to chase them down to get some assistance.
Still good pizzas and great service.
I’ve always had a good experience here. Food tastes fresh and very friendly employees. Very welcoming .i did not know Pizza Hut has gotten expensive though lol . But we work to eat!

Everytime I go there, everyone is so friendly. I would have given 5 stars but when I was in Pa and order for my son and daughter a delivery 2 miles in Berwyn Heights they said they don't deliver in that area.
So I had to order Dominoes
This Pizza Hut are very delicious better on Langley park and New Hampshire close to 495 this is the best I eat

Driver forgot my drink, was extremely rude, and refused to give me his name. I placed an online order to be delivered on Friday 2/14/20 @ 2pm. When the driver arrived he stated he had forgotten the pepsi but he still wanted the money for the order and that he would deduct the cost of the soda. I explained I still wanted the pepsi and since I gave him the full amount I wanted his name. He started walking away and said what do you want with my name? I asked again and he continued to refuse to give me his name. After he left just so there was no funny business I called up to the store to explain the situation to the manager. His tone sounded as if this was not the first time he has heard this complaint; he explained he would rush a soda out to me right away. About 20 min later the same man knocked at the door but instead of waiting for me to get to the door he left the sodas on the step and got in his car. The customer service at this location is terrible and drivers irresponsible without a care.
Thick and decadent frozen custard and their flavors of ice are on point. Can't go writing with a gelati, it's the best of both the I've and the custard worlds.
The ice cream is great but nothing special

It. Is. DELICIOUS. Fresh and/or creamy in any flavor combination you want. It's just the perfect treat for any hot day or bad day. Or any day you feel like having something sweet and fresh. Staff is always nice and the custard and the ice is always good.

It's the best Custard your going to find around here.  The water ice is good too, but the custard is my go-to.  Add on tje sprinkles for a nice little crunch to the mouth coating custard creamy goodness and you're set.

The following must be read with Anthony Bourdain’s voice in your head. (RIP)

Dear Rita’s

You often looked like somebody’s memory of a town, and the memory’s fading. You’re not open half the year, so I judged you to be running out of business, your counters to be dust-filled, and your ice cream to be drab. But on this especially humid day, one of the first of this summer, we decided to visit you almost as a joke. We told ourselves, “Even Rita’s can’t taste bad when we’re this tired.” “I’d eat a brick right now.” (undergrads, I tell ya)

As I stood outside the counters staring at your menu, I wondered why you would call your ice cream, a custard, and how full of yourself you must be to think Italian ice is better than any regular ice. Yet, I wanted to try both of them. The gelati seemed perfect, a choice of custard served over ice. Summer was finally here, and I’d been waiting to eat into some watermelon but here I was trying the watermelon ice and a twist custard of chocolate and vanilla.

I was so tired, I didn’t complain about how unflattering your cup looked. I dug right into the custard and took a bite and I realized immediately – you were no ordinary ice cream. To make sure it wasn’t just me being dehydrated, I took another bite. So thick, so creamy. It was almost like I wanted it to just stay in my mouth. Your chocolate was just the right amount of chocolat-y and as I finished it, I was already starting to taste the ice underneath it.

It was as though the custard was just to slowly build me up to something even better, so I don’t get completely blown away. Italian ice is no ordinary ice. How could something so different from a custard, taste so good with it? You left me with puzzling questions but instead of trying to think them through, I just decided to continue eating. But you weren’t done, were you?

During every dessert, there’s a point where you start feeling bad it’s almost over. I thought I was there but there was something creamy underneath the ice. Turns out, they had more custard underneath the ice!(!) I was probably close to tears. And I say probably only because I don’t want to admit it. I knew then, you were not just some ice cream place. You weren’t trying to make money, by feeding people. It wasn’t the custard, it wasn’t the ice. You were trying to make people happy. And for that, I’ll always come back.

X
Manny

Delicious food and a fun experience. Nice place to take a date. 
Service can be a tad slow and inconsistent, forgetting items and having to remind servers about my missing items,  but when they're busy I try to be patient. During dinnet for an additional $3 you can order unlimited sushi with hot pot!

I really like this place but I cannot lie it does have its flaws. I  thought I’d love this place because it was WAY closer to me than the other hot pots in MD. I don’t like how they changed their menu and took a couple of the things I loved off the menu. They also tend to run out of the BEST things! Also their hot base is EXTREMELY spicy!! No matter if you get the lowest level of spicy it is HOT! I can’t enjoy my food because it’s so spicy and I always say mild! Overall it is a decent place to visit but they def need to work on making their spicy base less spicy so we can actually be able to eat and enjoy the food!!

While I enjoyed my food, they really don't mess around with the spice!

Even the mildest level for the spicy broth was almost too much for me. The server was at least very honest about this, but I think they could dial it back a bit for the mildest option.

I love this place!! Been going here since they open and the flavor is still the same! Servers are very nice and they make sure you have everything you need! It can get busy during the weekend because it is in a college area but the wait shouldn’t be too long since they have plenty tables.

Brought my mother and nephew here for their first hotpot and they loved it! I love how they have dipping sauce recipes over the buffet. Ingredients are good and portion sizes very decent. The waiters came through often too.
I tried this place before with a friend and I am hooked since then. I enjoy the good vibes and yummy dishes and drinks. They never disappoint.
This place is one of my favorites! Fair prices, large dishes and the staff members are consistently super nice.

We came to this restaurant for lunch. we heard about this spot from many people.  Well, it was very successful. The staff welcomed us with a smile and we felt very good. The food was just great. We enjoyed every moment and we will definitely return to this restaurant. We recommend this place to all.

This place is unquestionably one of the best place in the region. Every time I go there I am highly happy. They maintain their high  level service and the highest level of cooking  they serve. You always win with this place. Very  recommended.
I adore this place a lot. theres a very nice air. The cuisine is great. the service is powerful and the crew is very professional. The price is honest. profoundly recommend.
I admire this place a lot. theres a great air. The meals are tasty. the service is powerful and the waiters are polite. The cost is reasonable. truly recommend.
Simple they are quick and easy for drive-thru. Using their app for good deals when the family wants BK.
This place clearly knows how to treat their clients. Always with a very nice attitude. The food is conveniently priced, constantly delicious and clean.

As an employee at this location, due to COVID-19, we have a lack of supplies & ingredients due to shipment delays, so please dont feel as though we are being"lazy" and/or just dont want to make something simply because we tell you we dont have it. We are currently out of onion rings, most desserts, and boxed juices & bottled drinks.
We apologize for the inconvenience and plan on helping you with all that we can.
If you want cold food go here and don't expect onion rings they will say there all out when there just to lazy to cook them
I would give them five stars, however, it is necessary to ask for extra cheese and meat in order to have a normal taco.
If my kids like it is approved so 5 star to customer service too keep it up

Very well organised and convenient restaurant. They serve big portions and for inexpensive prices. We enjoyed the menu very much and the staff members were super welcoming and explanatory. Highly recommended.

Broken credit card machine, we'd placed an order, paid and waited for about 15min before being asked if we were ready to order. We said we ordered, told the Young lady what we ordered & there was no record of it causing us to reorder and after checking my account I learned the initial transaction didn't go through, that's when the woman said oh yeah it's broken. Why the hell didn't you say that as you stood there watching us order?!?!?
Good  clean friendly staff....and they fast

Our waiter Jen was a pleasure. She did everything right and had a great personality. The food came fast and was delicious! Will definitely return when I need a good quick meal. Nice, clean, warm welcoming environment. I love the open kitchen. The aromas fill the room and you just can't wait to get your food. Two thumbs up all the way!
This spot is worth visiting. They serve big portions for convenient prices. Regularly neat and with awesome atmosphere. Highly recommended.
Good food. New burger menu is good. Seasoned fries option is even better.one should try the sizzlin skillet.

I came here with some 8 friends and we were not able to get seated. We waited 20 minutes and they served so many other groups and left us waiting. We requested to split our group to be able to get seated, but no action was taken. So, we left. Not the best service. I hope some positive changes are made!

Friendly staff, nice food, super large portion, good place to chat with a bunch of friends.
But the biscuit is terrible, way too salty.

Overpriced! That’s all you really need to know. Diner quality food and service trying to be upscale. The food and service was not bad, but it was not that good either (dirty wine glass, service was slow and the food was served warm not hot). If we were at a diner paying diner prices no problem, but a cheese burger was $15, French dip $17 both served with below average fries. Entrees were much more, cheapest appetizers were $8. There was no kids menu, but a very small basic plate of Mac & cheese was $8, apple juice another $5. At most places you could get both for $5.
Clearly they are trying to be a upscale grill, they have a nice (but expensive) wine list, and there are some elements of the atmosphere to match (like the bathroom & live jazz), but the booths are uncomfortable and the experience does not match the advertising. Family friendly, but clearly not designed with families in mind, I assume their main customers are people staying at the hotel above, but if you are a local I would not recommend it.

The service and food was great. I was actually surprised at how quickly the food came out and how well it was cooked. The jazz band was a nice touch and it was also nice to meet the owner who made sure we were well taken care of.

Went here for date night had the best time. Live music that night which only enhanced the meal.  Staff was super awesome and ther Es s an open kitchen so you can see your food being made. Really good size portions. Overall,  I will definitely be back.
Food was fantastic. Large portions. Upscale atmosphere. Parking garage. Dinner for four adults, two beers and tip was $150.

I admire this spot! They serve excellent food, they have a rich menu, The chef in that restaurant is very trained, I enjoy a lot eating all their dishes. The dishes are always fresh, the attitude toward
Salad was great, drink selection was a bit lackluster however. But the main point of the place: the salad, tastes delicious to your own personal craft. Thank you!!
Good food, but pretty pricey for what you get, imo.
How hard is it to make a salad? I asked for a guacamole greens and they gave it to me with no avocado....it was delivered via ubereats soooo yeah. great job sweetgreen. just lost a customer forever.

Due to the cov-id19 situation and the timeframe I ordered the food online, it was necessary for me to order the food online from the College Park Maryland Sweetgreen online for pickup if I wanted a Sweetgreen salad. By 640 pm  Monday March 16 2020 I ordered a Garden Cobb salad for pickup which came with avocado, roasted sweet potatoes, hard boiled egg, tomatoes, red onions, blue cheese, roasted almonds, organic mesclun, chopped romaine, balsamic vinaigrette. If you order the item to be pickedup through online portal notification is given in the email of the amount of minutes a person’s order is held after the order is ready for pickup (my email gave a 30 minute timeframe). I traveled at least 2 miles from where my husband and I currently live to pick up the salad and fortunately the salad still tasted delish by the time I received it. I paid for this salad with money made from my current place of employment though I keep an open mind to both paid professional reviewers and those who write reviews for free.
This location is always good. We enjoyed the new seasonal items and the classics as well. The guacamole greens counties to be my go-to salad. The place is always clean and the service is polite.

I understand working at 2 is not ideal, but if you are going to work represent your company well. The cashier tonight was going out of his way to be rude. Sorry you have to work late but it’s not my problem you signed up to work for a restaurant that stays open late. Please be more considerate to your paying customers.

I visited this McDonald's on a Saturday and even though the drive thru was packed, my food inside the restaurant got ready quick! There are enough parking, the servers are respectful and helpful. There is also a lot of tables to seat . The toilets are very small tho.
Their food is very good to the mouth.  And their chicken is very crispy and crunchy. Keep up the good work☺thumps up.
There fries are horrible they taste brunt and dry and too crunchy.

I had good service here. It took a little while for me to get my food while going through the drive through even though my order was pretty simple but there was a pretty long line inside. The fries were great though. Some of the best I've had from this chain. The location is kind of a pain to get to though with the median.

Very good food. I eat here often -- I usually get chicken with Yucca fries and plaintains, but I've tried the other sides too and they're all good. The folks who work there are always very nice.

(Food is available fast, and it's close to campus.)

This is small place with limited seating. The lady on the front greeted me very politely and the customer service was excellent. I got the half chicken with rice and plantains. The food taste was good. The sauces they gave were really good. Be careful the jalepeno sauce was too spicy.

This is a great restaurant! Charcoal Chicken was tasty, not too salty and well seasoned rice and beans were tasty and the fried plantains was sweet. *Overall the food was not satly at all* They have great costumer service and food. The lady at the front desk was very nice and made sure we were well taking care of. This is a nice place to hangout and eat with friends.
One of my preferred spots to eat. convenient location, always clean, and excellent customer service. I recommend this place!
You can get your food immediately. Pretty good for someone in hurry.

I just moved to the area not too long ago, so I am unfamiliar with the restaurant scene. Having ordered from this place twice for delivery, I can confidently say now that they have secured my future business. Food is phenomenal. Love the chicken parm sub, and the pizza is good too.
Great taste, nice people

I adore this spot! They serve splendid food, their menu is nice, The chef in that restaurant is very trained, I like a lot trying all their dishes. The food is always good, the attitude towards the clients  is agreeable. I  go often to this restaurant and I not even once was disappointed. I recommend this place.

Pizza and wings good. This is really to warn you to be careful with online ordering.  I made the mistake of not looking carefully at the site and ended up ordering through Eat Street and not the restaurant's site (I THOUGHT the site looked different but it had been a while since my last order). Anyway, I arrived to pick up my order and they had no record of it. They said they have no contract with Eat Street anymore, so it never got sent to the restaurant.  They made my order quickly but of course I had to pay them.  I got a credit from Eat Street on my credit card..PLUS Eat Street charged more for my PICKUP order.  Just make sure you use the Pizza Bolis site...learn from my mistake 😏

The service is mediocre.  The pizza is the same. Not the best pizza.  Do not order Garlic bread. It's just a regular French bread with butter and garlic powder on it. The picture on the menu is NOT the same for Garlic Bread. See picture of their Garlic bread. 

I didn't try anything else but I highly suggest dont order it.

Also you will have go hunt for your toppings. They are that scattered.

My first time in any "Pho" place.  My group and I were passing by and the cold weather called for some "hot soup."  The place obviously wasn't vying for a spot in any glossy mag; it was what one would expect of a "campus hangout" -- kinda "well-worn" and a little gritty.  The crew seemed "carefree" -- there was no effort to look "efficient, organized, and professional."  Despite those, the food was surprisingly good.  We loved everything!  We were thoroughly satisfied.  (Going back to dine here is a big possibility.)

Excellent and friendly customer service.They have good options for vegetarians. Their Pad thai and Bangkok noodles are a good option for those who prefer vegetarian.Serve large bowls at reasonable rates.Have happy hours every monday to Friday 3pm to 5pm. Refer photos for details. Definitely recommended if you are a noodle lover and travel to college park area.
The Pho comes quick and hot and it's tasty every single time I get it. Highly recommend the Thai iced tea to wash it all down.  The chicken wings are great also.

Customer service was excellent. Food was delicious. Portions big enough for two. 
Grill chicken vermicelli bowl. Fried chicken wings
The ambience is great. It is a cozy place with nice service. The food is delicious. I have tried various items on the menu and was never disappointed. The Bangkok noodles are my fav.
This place gives great service and delightful food. The best restaurant around here. The food and drinks came out quickly and the rates were inexpensive. Recommended.
Fast and flavorful
Rude latina; not cut out to perform customer service

The food is pretty subpar. I have had better tasting Chinese food from cheap Chinese restaurant. My public schools made more delicious orange chicken. After all the hype of this place, and trying it about 4 times to really get a taste of to the restaurants best, I'm pretty disappointed. The orange chicken is pretty bad but the Beijing beef, surprisingly is really nice. Skip on the ever-praised orange chicken and try something else.
Great food. Loved the fried rice.
Food is nothing special I am told. Great friendly meet up spot and easy access from the road. Wind tunnel and close to the border campus food.
Much better than the average college dining all. Better variety, better quality.
Don't eat red meat here you will get sick and you will suffer
It is worth your money. But at the same time you get what you paid for.
Pretty good food as cafeterias go

Less than 2 weeks ago, I stopped by the Adele H Stamp Student Union Building via the University of Maryland College Park campus to get a breakfast sandwich from McDonald’s My husband and I have been to this place multiple times. The building has a food court area that has multiple eating places Mcdonald’s, Sbarro’s, Panda Express, Qdoba, Chic Fil A, Maryland Dairy etc. There is also a bookstore that carries a multiple variety of books and a coffee place. There are also multiple chairs to sit andor relax during the day, however obviously peak times influence how crowded the place can get.
Home of the National History Day contest and they do an awesome jobs hosting the event. Staff is very helpful.
'Centre' of campus. The STAMP is the place for students meetings and stuff like that. You can find many eateries here. It's a really cool place to be. Nice facility with high tech stuff
Nice facility. Many large multifunction rooms. Modern tech with video screens from the ceiling, and full computer integration.
It has a good selection of fast food. Interesting decorations. Good ice cream at the dairy store. Lots of students having a good time. Good place to get sports clothes.

Much better than the average college dining all. Better variety, better quality.

It is worth your money. But at the same time you get what you paid for.
Pretty good food as cafeterias go

Service is great, i have been there a couple of times over the last 2 months, usually same servers.
The food is good, could be better. I had steak tacos.
Reasonable prices.
Such the best experience starting with Rocio our waitress. This is a must try restaurant and prices are affordable. I encourage anyone to try it you won't regret it.

I like this place and the people are very nice. I’m not sure if the cook was tired or because I came in really late because they did a terrible job on my no cheese pupusas. I could have done a better job making fried corn flower pancakes at home. They could have at least added salt and pepper

I ordered two carne asadas here and were absolutely dry nothing juicy about it 
The only thing i likes about it was the pupusas and horchata otherwise I won’t be buying her again

Delicious pupusas! Hot, fresh, melt in your mouth goodness. It's easy to get stuffed here and not break the bank.

The steamed corn tamales with sweet crema are addicting. And the beef soup is rich and flavorful.
Finest food, very friendly employees, consistently excellent vibes. They charge reasonable prices and the food quality is good. Keep it up.

I meet friends in this restaurant often! This is the best place to have a bite.  I go to this spot regularly. The food is excellent, the staff members are welcoming and the price is good. I like being in this place to have a tasty meal.
Great sushi, but for the love of God try some new things. Like this mango dragon roll
First time to be in there. Food and serve is good. Near campus and easy to access. Total on the picture with tax and fee was 58.
Had a very good experience here with my kids. The food comes fast and the customer service is just great. Prices are fair.

D.P. Dough is a legend in this area. I visited just this week, and I was super thankful that they're open later than most places, cooking up fresh to order calzones. I got the classic, Combat Zone (no mushrooms), and it was fast, hot and delicious! Service was friendly and helpful, and they were playing solid tunes inside while I waited for my food to bake. Thanks to everyone at D.P. Dough. I'll be back for lunch, and one of the Calzones of the day deals, soon.
This place obviously knows how to take care of their clients. Regularly with a very kind attitude. The food is fairly priced, always delightful and clean.
Best place to go when youre smashed. Im sure its great when youre sober too

I always get buffer zone from here. It's really good. I've tried couple of others. They're pretty good too. Their quality is always consistent. Never had a bad experience. If you pick up, it's a 15 minutes wait. If you get it delivered, the wait is about 45 minutes
In College Park, MD gets you fat boy/girl full. Not as good as the ones from Rhode Island 20yrs ago yet still tasty

I come to this marvelous  restaurant every couple of days since I like the ambiance that is part of this place. The team is exceptionally attentive and professional. The service is certainly fast. Needless to say, the food you get is outstanding. I came often and I was never disappointed. The expense is modest. I highly suggest this place to my friends and family.

It's really good spicy desi food for the people of central Asia and you will get buffet for reasonable cost. In the buffet you see different varieties in both veg and non veg. Here Kebabs are famous with different choices like fish, chicnen, meat and all...
I love this place very much. there is a friendly feeling. The meals are good. the service is dynamic and the personel is friendly. The cost is modest. I definitely recommend.

This isn't a good option if you are looking for Indian vegetarian dishes. The vegetarian dishes they had were average and they had no special dish or sweet in the buffet. The sitting area is clean and spacious though.
Exceptional food, kind staff members, always  awesome ambience. They charge reasonable prices and the food quality is very good. Keep it up.
